---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base 
  title="Metalsmith LoRA — Aarik Wells" 
  description="A micro-dataset FLUX LoRA trained on photos of a bespoke physical ring to rapidly prototype new jewelry designs."
>
  <main class="case-study">
    <!-- Hero Strip -->
    <section class="cs-hero">
      <h1>Metalsmith LoRA</h1>
      <p class="cs-subtitle">A micro-dataset FLUX LoRA trained on photos of a bespoke physical ring to rapidly prototype new jewelry designs.</p>
      
      <p class="cs-tags">
        <code>FLUX · LoRA · Product Design · Dataset Curation</code>
      </p>
      
      <div class="cs-cta">
        <a href="#" class="btn btn--primary">View on Civitai</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Problem -->
    <section class="cs-section">
      <h3>The Problem</h3>
      <p class="cs-large">I had designed and fabricated a unique copper and silver ring. I wanted to see what other pieces of jewelry (like a bangle) would look like in this exact style—before committing the time and materials to build them.</p>
      
      <p>Prototyping physical jewelry is expensive and time-consuming. I realized that if I could train a model on the specific design language of my ring, I could rapidly generate and evaluate new form factors in that style. The constraint? Since it was a single physical object, I was limited to a micro-dataset of just 10 to 15 unique images.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- The Build -->
    <section class="cs-section">
      <h3>The Execution & Direction</h3>
      <p>Training a model on such a small dataset requires immense precision. I had to ensure that the dataset curation and captioning were flawless so the model learned the *technique* and *style* rather than over-fitting to the specific shape of a ring.</p>
      
      <p>I successfully trained a FLUX LoRA that captured the bespoke copper and silver aesthetic. The model extrapolated the design language perfectly, generating high-quality renders of bangles and other jewelry pieces using the very same technique.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- The Takeaway -->
    <section class="cs-section">
      <h3>What this proves</h3>
      
      <p>This project proves that AI isn't just for generating digital art; it is a highly practical tool for <strong>industrial design and rapid prototyping</strong>. By bridging my physical craftsmanship as a metalsmith with my technical capability in model fine-tuning, I created a system that drastically reduces the iteration time for physical product design.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Closing -->
    <section class="cs-section cs-center" style="margin-top: 4rem;">
      <div class="cs-cta">
        <a href="#" class="btn btn--primary">Explore the model on Civitai</a>
        <a href="/#work" class="btn btn--secondary">← Back to Projects</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .case-study {
    --bg: #0C0C0E; --text: #EDEDEF; --accent: #D4A853; --muted: #6B7B8D;
    --font-display: "Space Grotesk", system-ui, sans-serif;
    --font-mono: "JetBrains Mono", ui-monospace, monospace;
    
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    color: var(--text);
  }
  
  .cs-hero { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 4rem; }
  .cs-hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .cs-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2vw, 1.4rem);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }
  
  .cs-tags {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .cs-tags code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(212, 168, 83, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(212, 168, 83, 0.25);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
  }
  
  .cs-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .cs-section h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .cs-section h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  
  .cs-large {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  
  .cs-section ul {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .cs-section li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  .cs-center { text-align: center; }
  
  .cs-cta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  
  .btn {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 0.8rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
  }
  .btn--primary {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #0C0C0E;
  }
  .btn--primary:hover { transform: translateY(-2px); }
  .btn--secondary {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--text);
    border: 1px solid #2A2A30;
  }
  .btn--secondary:hover { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent); }
</style>
